===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} ''sisoures'' (attested since 1350–1400), from {{etyl|fro|en}} ''cisoires'', from {{etyl|VL.|en}} ''*cīsōria'', plural of {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|cīsōrium||cutting tool}} (compare {{term|chisel}}); from {{etyl|la|en}} word root ''-cīsus'' (compare {{term|excise}}) or {{term|cæsus}}, past participle of {{term|cædere||to cut}}.
* The current spelling, from the 16th century, is due to association with {{etyl|ML.|en}} ''scissor'' (“tailor”), from {{etyl|la|en}} carrying the meaning “carver, cutter”, from {{term|scindere||to split|lang=la}}.

